The paper deals with shape abstraction and modeling, which are topics related to computer graphics (cs.CG) and geometric modeling (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the use of medial balls to encode shape information, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes applications for the generated shapes, which involve mechanical rigidity and control (cs.SY).
